# Exercise 007 - Create a custom template

1) As developer user create a new project named "template-test". Export the oc
   new-app output in yaml format using the GitHub repo
   https://github.com/mmul-it/docker with the context dir ncat-msg-http-port
   and the name "my-template" in a new yaml file;

2) Edit the file replacing everything necessary to make it a Template with
   three parameters: NAME, REPLICAS and PORT;

3) Add the parameters section with default values and descriptions for each
   parameter;

4) Create the template and check if parameters are defined correctly;

5) Deploy a new app from this template. Check if everyting is ok and follow the
   BuildConfig;

6) Expose the new app and check from a browser if works;

7) Deploy, expose and check a new app from the same template;
